Judgment in the assault case of EFF leader Julius Malema and  MP Mbuyiseni Ndlozi is expected on June 3. Malema and Ndlozi are charged with assaulting a police officer, Lt-Col Johannes Jacobus Venter, at the funeral of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela in April 2018. The incident was captured on CCTV footage. They have pleaded not guilty. On Friday, a final state witness who had been expected to testify failed to arrive at the Randburg magistrateâ€™s court. The state requested a further postponement, but the defence argued there have been several postponements already. After a short adjournment, the court said judgment would be handed down at their next appearance. The defence has been granted until May 13 to submit heads of arguments while the state has until May 20 to submit its arguments. TimesLIVE